channel.title: Javascript is enabled, idk why it wont let me see movies! or games!
channel.description: can someone help me, ok you know java script? well. for some odd reason, when i go onto youtube,addicting games, or anything else that displays movies it says "you have java script turned off or you have an old version of the flash player." my java script was already enabled, i made sure of that. but, it wont let me download the flash player so i don't know. it is wierd. but it says! "internet explorer has blocked this site from using an activex control in an unsafe manner. as a result, this page may not display correctly" when i right click that banner at the top of my browser it says two things "whats the risk? and more information." niether of them tell me how to download it.. i don't know my computer is acting wierd for some reason, if people know why one out of two of those reasons are contact me immedietly by obviously displaying a comment on here.. :confused: [br][size=1]Posted on: October 08, 2007, 01:48:30 AM[/size][hr][quote="god of huckalu"]can someone help me, ok you know java script? well. for some odd reason, when i go onto youtube,addicting games, or anything else that displays movies it says "you have java script turned off or you have an old version of the flash player." my java script was already enabled, i made sure of that. but, it wont let me download the flash player so i don't know. it is wierd. but it says! "internet explorer has blocked this site from using an activex control in an unsafe manner. as a result, this page may not display correctly" when i right click that banner at the top of my browser it says two things "whats the risk? and more information." niether of them tell me how to download it.. i don't know my computer is acting wierd for some reason, if people know why one out of two of those reasons are contact me immedietly by obviously displaying a comment on here.. :confused:[/quote][br][size=1]Posted on: October 08, 2007, 01:57:26 AM[/size][hr][quote="god of huckalu"]I have java script enabled, and i cant download the fricking flash player for some reason - that's part of why i need fricking help![/quote] [/quote]
